misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes they must save the last element, move all elements one index to the right from the end toward the start, then place the saved last element at index 0.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No conceptual gap detected. This matches Java’s array assignment semantics (overwriting elements) and the required right-rotation by one with wrap-around.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: No error; produces correct output for N>=0. Handles N=0 safely by skipping the shift loop and printing an empty shifted array.
